The paper deals with image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of probabilistic models and machine learning techniques to decompose images into homogeneous surfaces suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of Chebyshev inequality, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
